-- Brazil Stock Movers: Pao de Acucar, Petrobras Gain; Vale Slides
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-01-12T20:34:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/brazil-stock-movers-pao-de-acucar-petrobras-gain-vale-slides.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close. Preferred shares are
usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  index fell 0.1 percent to 59,920.78.  Cia. Brasileira de Distribuicao Grupo Pao de Acucar  (PCAR4
BS),  Brazil ’s biggest retailer, rose 2.1 percent to 69.49 reais.
Total sales increased 20 percent to 15.1 billion reais ($8.5
billion) in the fourth quarter, the company said in a regulatory
filing today.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  (PETR4 BS) gained 0.7 percent to
23.08 reais. The state-controlled  oil company  said proven
reserves rose 2.7 percent last year to 16.4 billion barrels of
oil equivalent, according to standards set by Brazil’s oil
regulator.  Vale SA (VALE5)  (VALE5 BS) slid 1.1 percent to 39.36 reais. The
world’s largest iron-ore producer said it will lose 2 million
metric tons of the steelmaking ingredient due to heavy rains in
three Brazilian states.  To contact the reporter on this story:
